criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  plantar heel pain diagnosed clinically and instrumentally (ultrasound) as plantar
             fasciitis, that has not responded to conservative treatment for at least six months;

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  History of previous fractures or ankle and heel surgery;

          -  Recurrence of previous local painful episodes;

          -  Lesion of the plantar fascia on US examination;

          -  Presence of pathologies that affect the function of the foot (lumbar radiculopathy,
             Achilles tendinitis, Morton's neuroma, etc.);

          -  Chronic inflammatory conditions such as psoriasis, psoriatic arthritis,
             spondyloarthritis, ankylosing spondylitis, rheumatoid arthritis, chronic inflammatory
             bowel disease.
